00:48:29.830 --> 00:48:34.040
She opts to switch back and forth
between the masculine pronoun

00:48:34.040 --> 00:48:36.420
and the feminine, this
in recognition

00:48:36.420 --> 00:48:42.220
of Irouso's [phonetic] constant
crossing of gender boundaries.

00:48:42.220 --> 00:48:45.880
Irouso was born in Northern Spain,

00:48:45.880 --> 00:48:48.000
was sent to the convent
very quickly.

00:48:48.000 --> 00:48:52.820
At the age of 14, she escaped from
the convent, dressed as a man,

00:48:52.820 --> 00:48:57.520 position:56%
assumed the name "Francisco Loyola,"
and lived his life from that point

00:48:57.520 --> 00:49:02.070
on as a man, moving to the New
World, getting into bar brawls,

00:49:02.070 --> 00:49:04.700
getting very close
to marrying as well.

00:49:04.700 --> 00:49:08.290
Coming back to Spain, after
having been discovered

00:49:08.290 --> 00:49:17.390
as not really being a -- having
the masculine gender at birth,

00:49:17.390 --> 00:49:22.570
that's a good way to put it, he
was brought before the Inquisition.

00:49:22.570 --> 00:49:26.010 position:56%
