can read closely --

00:49:40.790 --> 00:49:42.790
and I've left it in the
Spanish because we lose it

00:49:42.790 --> 00:49:45.680 position:56%
in the translation into the English,

00:49:45.680 --> 00:49:49.000
she begins the text,
"[Speaks Spanish].

00:49:49.000 --> 00:49:52.740 position:56%
I was born Dona Catalina de Irouso."

00:49:52.740 --> 00:49:55.760
A little further on,
"Y yo muchahca."

00:49:55.760 --> 00:49:58.290
She had an encounter
with another nun

00:49:58.290 --> 00:49:59.810
who would abuse her in the convent.

00:49:59.810 --> 00:50:03.500
"Y yo muchacha," and
"I, a young girl."

00:50:03.500 --> 00:50:08.020
But there's a point in the
text when Irouso assumes,

00:50:08.020 --> 00:50:09.830
embraces a masculine identity.

00:50:09.830 --> 00:50:15.260
And what's curious is that the
pronoun changes at that point.

00:50:15.260 --> 00:50:17.140
And he says, "[Speaks Spanish].

00:50:17.140 --> 00:50:24.910
When I entered [inaudible],"
using the masculine, "entrado."

00:50:24.910 --> 00:50:26.210
Further on, "[Speaks Spanish].

00:50:26.210 --> 00:50:31.030
I named myself, I embraced
this gender."

00:50:31.030 --> 00:50:35.480
And who are we to determine
the gender of Irouso?

00:50:35.480 --> 00:50:38.990
Who are we even to impose the
moniker, [speaks Spanish],

00:50:38.990 --> 00:50:43.590
which keeps his gender
indeterminate.

00:50:43.590 --> 00:50:45.930
No, no; Irouso made
the determination.

00:50:45.930 --> 00:50:47.830
Irouso embraced gender.

00:50:47.830 --> 00:50:49.780
Irouso lived the gender.

00:50:49.780 --> 00:50:54.360 position:56%
And to my mind, we need to return to
these stories, multiple stories --

00:50:54.360 --> 00:50:59.630
if you read the inquisitorial
documentation, multiple stories

00:50:59.630 --> 00:51:04.600
about subjects from the
past making determinations

00:51:04.600 --> 00:51:08.010
about their own sexual
and/or gender identity.

00:51:08.010 --> 00:51:11.580
We need to return to
this documentation

00:51:11.580 --> 00:51:16.930
and really bring contemporary
trans-theory to bear

00:51:16.930 --> 00:51:18.740
on these subjects from the past.

00:51:18.740 --> 00:51:20.300
So that's certainly
one of the directions

00:51:20.300 --> 00:51:26.040
that a newly-invigorated
queer Iberia project,

00:51:26.040 --> 00:51:29.320
one of the areas we need to explore

00:51:29.320 --> 00:51:31.960
with greater verb,
as Joe has put it.

00:51:31.960 --> 00:51:33.260
&gt;&gt; Josiah Blackmore: Yes, yes.

00:51:33.260 --> 00:51:36.670
