get to the end of the Middle Ages

00:51:36.670 --> 00:51:40.200
and the transition into
the early modern period,

00:51:40.200 --> 00:51:43.740
the trans-Atlantic enterprise,

00:51:43.740 --> 00:51:47.980
which offers some very
interesting possibilities, I think,

00:51:47.980 --> 00:51:53.610
on the Portuguese side of things
-- I'm thinking of a fairly old

00:51:53.610 --> 00:51:58.900
but still definitional book Richard
Trexler's, "Sex of Conquest."

00:51:58.900 --> 00:52:04.140
I'm think of [speaks French],
