sin with other women."

00:54:35.290 --> 00:54:41.670
What's interesting here, though,
is that it's still conceived

00:54:41.670 --> 00:54:47.040
of as an active sin,
as an active act.

00:54:47.040 --> 00:54:56.350
In other words, the one who was
sinful in this act is the woman

00:54:56.350 --> 00:55:00.440
who penetrates the other woman.

00:55:00.440 --> 00:55:08.340
So it's still understood in
terms of an active sodomy,

00:55:08.340 --> 00:55:13.060
of a woman's appropriation
of the male prerogative.

00:55:13.060 --> 00:55:16.040
So there's so much more to
be teased out of these texts,

00:55:16.040 --> 00:55:17.700
so much more that we need to do.

00:55:17.700 --> 00:55:23.190 position:56%
Not only in terms of our archaeology
of queer subjectivities in the past,

00:55:23.190 --> 00:55:25.210
